title: Jason Priestley responds to Tori Spelling’s 90210 sex claims
text:
JASON Priestley is not happy that former co-star Tori Spelling is spilling the beans on their 90210-era sexual encounters.
But he’s not denying the two did the deed, either.
When asked by a follower on Twitter if Spelling’s claim the two had sex back in the day was true or false, Priestley replied: “I’m not getting into this … It’s nobody’s business … Either way …”
He then tweeted a second time, clarifying his stance on the subject: “I’m only speaking with negativity about the Lifetime movie and Tori’s lie detector … Nothing but love for 90210.”
Spelling, 42, made the claim that she slept with Priestley, 46, on Lifetime’s new show Celebrity Lie Detector.
After admitting last week that she had a long relationship with fellow cast member Brian Austin Green, who recently split from Megan Fox, Spelling was pressed by the show’s host Louise Roe whether “there [is] anyone else from the original cast that you had sex with.”

Rendezview 0 comments Terror raids over Sydney shooting Crime School prayers are in the spotlight Nsw ‘Let the blood flow on the street’ Nsw ‘Her boyfriend was already engaged’ Relationships Spelling said she hadn’t slept with Ian Ziering or Luke Perry, but claimed she had in fact slept with Priestley.
“It was a summer fling; it was offset,” she said. “It was our version of a summer romance. The 90210 version. And that was it, and we stayed great friends.”
“Oh my God, I’m gonna get in so much trouble for this,” she added.
Jason Priestley and Tori Spelling with the cast of 90210. This article first appeared in the New York Post .
Originally published as Priestley shoots back at Tori’s sex claims
